    "created_at": "2013-04-13T04:16:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-04-13T04:16:08Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "So the behavior work fine, but @juliantaylor has a good point that if ipython is installed using setuptools, these scripts are not used, but instead the setuptools entry points are used which are listed here:\n\nhttps://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/setupbase.py#L313\n\nWe need to design this so the exception handling logic is trigger regardless of how the apps are run.  Maybe create a decorator that handles this that all of the entry points can be decorated with?  Then we could just all the entry points without worrying about repeating the logic in each place.\n"
  },
